result.execSummary:
All charges against Rodney A Clendening in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Rodney A Clendening is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

State calls Capital Police Det. B. Kaiser, sworn. Direct.  Officer identifies defendant. Cross. Marked exhibit 1 and 2. Re-direct.  Re-cross.  Witness excused.  State calls City of Madison Officer M. G. Thomson, sworn. Direct. Officer identifies defendant. Officer excused.  State moves for bind over, makes argument. Defense moves for exhibits 1 and 2 to be admitted.  State objects to exhibit 1.  Rebuttal by Atty. Chung. Court admits exhibits 1 and 2.  Court does take judicial notice that these are part of the court files, as they are signature bonds.  Defense objects to bend over, argues and requests case be dismissed. Rebuttal by State. Rebuttal by Defense. CT: has not found probable cause, and dismisses case.
